    {
      "id": "state-token-schema-port-map",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "How Ports Would Map",
      "position": {
        "x": 1900,
        "y": -160
      },
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "width": 440,
      "height": 360,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# How Ports Would Map\n\n## Idle\n- low opacity\n- no bright fill\n- minimal border contrast\n- no white outline\n\n## Hover\n- slight scale increase\n- brighter border\n- optional subtle label reveal\n\n## Selected host\n- port inherits some selected emphasis from host\n- should not outshout focused items elsewhere\n\n## Focused host / focused port\n- strongest ordinary contrast\n- clear attachment point\n\n## Drag target\n- strongest temporary port state\n- magnetic / receptive emphasis\n\n## Connected\n- occupied, but calmer than hover or drag target",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
